
- Download SonarQube from https://www.sonarqube.org/downloads/
- Downloaded version will come in Zip, just unzip it
- Goto /sonarcube/bin/<platform-folder>
- Hit startsonar.bat to start running SonarQube on server
- Now open http://localhost:9000 to see admin panel of SonarQube
- Login to user panel using “admin” for username and password
- Create a project on Sonarqube panel
- During project creation you have to select a project key, and you will get a login hash code for the project
- Run this command after implementation of gradle part in app.gradle: gradlew clean test jacocoTestReport sonarqube -Dsonar.projectKey=yourprojectkey -Dsonar.sources=. -Dsonar.host.url=http://localhost:9000 -Dsonar.login=yourprojecthash
- e.g.: gradlew clean test jacocoTestReport sonarqube -Dsonar.projectKey=weatherapp -Dsonar.sources=. -Dsonar.host.url=http://localhost:9000 -Dsonar.login=bf344592d8c309f7498c3a0a0a11dc09c5b8fd2d


